      "insights": [
        "ו/ישכן (vayishken) — and he placed — The Hebrew verb 'sh-k-n' (שכן) means 'to dwell' or 'to tabernacle,' carrying a connotation of God's presence settling, not merely a spatial 'placing,' yet English translations flatten this to a simple 'placed,' losing the hint that God's presence now dwells at the east to guard the way."
